diff:1580912506:1580910795:=3c3%0a%3c !%25center%25%25mortal%25'''''"Well Behaved Women Rarely Make History"'''''%0a---%0a> !%25center%25%25mortal%25'''''"Art Is Not Subjective"'''''%0a9c9%0a%3c (:cell width=400:) The Hermetic Sisterhood%0a---%0a> (:cell width=400:) The Providence Of Muses%0a11c11%0a%3c (:cell width=400:) [[https://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/[[PamalaSalam|Pamela Salam]]%0a---%0a> (:cell width=400:) [[https://wantonwicked.gamingsandbox.com/wiki/?n=Players.AnastasiaVorobyova|Anastasia Vorobyova]]%0a13c13%0a%3c (:cell width=400:) Education%0a---%0a> (:cell width=400:) Arts and Society%0a15c15%0a%3c (:cell width=400:) The Philosophers Stone%0a---%0a> (:cell width=400:) The Fresco of the Greek Muses%0a17c17%0a%3c (:cell width=400:) &#913;&#935;&#937; Sorority House%0a---%0a> (:cell width=400:) The Temple of Passion%0a19c19%0a%3c (:cell width=400:)  Feminism%0a---%0a> (:cell width=400:)  Perfecting the Form of Art%0a21c21%0a%3c (:cell width=400:) Young and Ambitious %0a---%0a> (:cell width=400:)The Proliferation of Art Through High Society%0a23c23%0a%3c (:cell width=400:) %0a---%0a> (:cell width=400:)Holding the Reins of Culture in Miami%0a27,28c27,29%0a%3c The Hermetic Sisterhood is a secret society of young and gifted women that exists to help each one to achieve its greatest and most profound potential. Built on concepts of Hermetic Philosophy and Alchemy its members seek to perfect themselves and transform to a higher level of success, knowledge, power, or whatever it is they seek. The society seeks to use their combined ability to even the scales of an unforgiving and unfair world, one set against young women from achieving the success and respect the members seek. Through occult and philosophical principles,  devout loyalty, and burning passion the Sisters will first transform themselves, but also the world%0a%3c %0a---%0a> The Providence of Muses is a mysterious organization that hearkens to the ancient Hellenic mythology, the Muses of the cult taking on the roles as living embodiments of creativity. They guide aspiring artists to greatness, demanding constant improvement in pursuit of sublimity of the arts. They hold up the philosophies of Plato as one of their guiding principles, the idea of the Forms — the non-physical, perfected essence of every object or idea in the world. It is the artist's purpose to find the Form of their work, the quintessential representation of the subject in their art; a rose more perfect than any rose; a song more melodious than any other song; passion more intense than any other passion; or hatred more caustic than any other hatred. The Muses inspire this perfection, they demand it, finding the potential that exists in budding artists and raising it out of the stifling shallows of mediocracy.%0a> %0a> But in this world, the pursuit of perfection in art is a meaningless purpose in itself unless that very art is held up as the shining example for others to follow. The Muses seek to exert influence over Miami's cultural life, and in order to do so they need a platform for their voice to be heard. And so they sought the company of the distinguished and refined in society, those with a palate and and an appreciation for quality in the artistic pursuits, inviting them into their fold. It is a powerful union, the creators and their patrons, determined to make Miami the very center of art and culture in America and in the world. %0a
